My bash configuration.

To get started:
1. Apply settings/simple.theme
1. ln -s /full/path/to/bashrc ~/.bashrc
1. ln -s /full/path/to/bash_profile ~/.bash_profile
1. ln -s /full/path/to/bash ~/.bash
1. ln -s /full/path/to/inputrc ~/.inputrc
1. chmod 755 ~/.bash/bin/*
1. Install iTerm2
1. Configure iTerm2 to use the config in ./iterm2 folder
1. Install Brew
1. brew tap Homebrew/brewdler
1. brew brewdle
1. Install JRE and JDK
1. Install rbenv-gem-rehash, rbenv-bundle-exec

After running brew install bash, you can change the default shell safely by:
1. Add /usr/local/bin/bash to /etc/shells
2. Running chsh -s /usr/local/bin/bash.
